---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MailchimpForm from '../components/MailchimpForm.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="What is Bachata? History, Music & Dance"
  description="Bachata is a romantic music and dance style from the Dominican Republic. Discover its roots, culture and why it is now danced all over the world."
  lang="en"
  lcpImage="/images/2024/04/320A0509-social-thumbnail.jpg"
>
  <div class="page-header" style="--page-hero-img: url('/images/2024/04/320A0509-social-thumbnail.jpg')">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>What is bachata?</h1>
      <p>A genre of music and dance from the Dominican Republic</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bio-content">
        <p style="font-size:1.1rem;">
          Bachata is a genre of music and social dance originating from the Dominican Republic.
          Nowadays, Bachata is a global phenomenon danced all around the world.
        </p>
        <p>
          Bachata has evolved from bolero, son and merengue and is usually danced with partners.
          The music is characterised by its distinctive guitar sound and the way the rhythm
          guides your movement.
        </p>
        <p>
          There are several styles of Bachata danced today — from the original Traditional style
          (also called Dominican Bachata), to Bachata Moderna and Bachata Sensual, each with its
          own flavour, technique and music.
        </p>

        <div style="margin-top:2rem;">
          <a href="/dance-with-us/" class="btn btn-primary">Learn to dance with us</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <MailchimpForm lang="en" />
</Layout>
